snippet: The Eisenhower Tree was removed from the 17th hole this weekend because of damage from an ice storm, the club said.
abstract: Eisenhower Tree, among the most famous trees in golf, is removed from the 17th hole at Augusta National Golf Club, site of the revered Masters tournament, because of damage it incurred during an ice storm.
lead_paragraph: The Eisenhower Tree was removed from the 17th hole this weekend because of damage from an ice storm, the club said.
